subjectkey: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
src_subject_id: Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
interview_age: Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
interview_date: Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
race_c: Race in two category (white only vs. other)
hispanic: Is subject of Hispanic, Latino, or Spanish origin?
exacer: Has patient been hospitalized or required crisis stabilization services in the past three months for any mental health problem?
td: Does the patient now meet Schooler-Kane criteria for probable tardive dyskinesia?
sigother: Are you currently living with a significant other?
demo4a: "If patient did not finish high school, years of education"
educ_yrs: Number of Years of Patient's Education
par_educ: How far did your parents go in school
demo5a: "If parent did not finish highschool, years of education"
qol01d: Currently live with a son or daughter
qol01f: Currently live with other people not related and not friends
yrs_trt: Years Since First Treatment for Behavioral or Emotional Problem
yrs_pres: Years Since First Prescribed an Antipsychotic Medication
me3: Did the patient have a hysterectomy?
me3a: 3a. Did the hysterectomy include an ooph
dema6: Which Best describes your current living situation?
dema7: In the past week, how many days did you get to choose what you had to eat for your meals. (Applies to MOST meals in a day)
dema9: Did you earn a high school diploma or GED?
